differences between bios efi MBR bootloader grub

image search: linux distribution timeline
install/remove/upgrade: apt-get install/remove/upgrade program name
search: apt-cache search key word
check  locally and remotely: apt-cache policy key word
install locally: dpkg -i program_file_name.deb

file permitions and ownship:
chown owner:group file_name 
chmod 644 file_name
rm -rf dir_name
mv、touch、cp、mkdir 
find dir_name_in_which_we_are_going_to_find -type [fd] -[i]name "some pattern" -perm 0644 -size [+-][0-9][kMG] -not -maxdepth [1-9] [-exec another command {} +]

find things in files: grep
grep [-in] "pattern" files_to_find 
tee: pipe the result to a file while output it on the screen at the same time
top: show  realtime applications
ps: show the entile list of running processes 
pgrep: show the process id of following application name
kill -9: kill the app of the following process id
killall [process_name]: kill all instances 

services: special types of linux processes 
service: service [service_name] action_we_want_the_service_to_to
alternative way of start/stop/restart/.. a service: systemctl action service_name 

schedule the task: 
contab: m h dom mon dow command

code::blocks: ide for c\c++\fortran
jet brains: ide with same style for various languages

git:
install git on Ubuntu: apt-get install git git-extras

